[SN]TITLE[SN]
Sprowston shop staff threatened in armed robbery

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Staff at a convenience store were left shaken after a man threatened them with a firearm and stole a large quantity of money.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The armed robbery happened in Sprowston, near Norwich, just before 21:00 BST on Saturday.
The man entered PJ's Convenience Stores in Linacre Avenue and threatened female members of staff.
He is is described as 5ft 4 tall, of stocky build, wearing dark clothing and a balaclava. No one was injured.
